Chris, Nathan, Frank

Week 7 Version

############ DESCRIPTION ############

PlaceMap plots places-of-interest along a route.

The current version is XHTML/Javascript based and uses Google Maps.

########### USAGE ##############

The htmljs/ directory contains the necessary XHTML and Javascript files to view the map. 

########### CONFIGURATION LOG ###########

The configuration log required for week 3 is in

log/git.log


THE FOLLOWING IS FOR THE JAVA VERSION IS NOT CURRENTLY BEING DEVELOPED

############ COMPILING ############

Running make will compile the required classes. lib contains required external libraries. Make is the prefered method due to the current volatility of the source.

make

OR (FOR LINUX)

javac -cp 'lib/*' org/placemap/datasource/MapQuest.java org/placemap/datasource/GooglePlaces.java org/placemap/datasource/URL2String.java org/placemap/tests/Test1.java org/placemap/tests/Google.java org/placemap/tests/TextUI.java org/placemap/tests/PlacesOnRoute.java org/placemap/Configuration.java org/placemap/entity/Location.java org/placemap/entity/Route.java org/placemap/entity/Address.java org/placemap/PlaceMap.java

OR (FOR WINDOWS)

javac -cp "lib\*" org\placemap\datasource\MapQuest.java org\placemap\datasource\GooglePlaces.java org\placemap\datasource\URL2String.java org\placemap\tests\Test1.java org\placemap\tests\Google.java org\placemap\tests\TextUI.java org\placemap\tests\PlacesOnRoute.java org\placemap\Configuration.java org\placemap\entity\Location.java org\placemap\entity\Route.java org\placemap\entity\Address.java org\placemap\PlaceMap.java

############ PLACES ON ROUTE APP ############

org.placemap.tests.PlacesOnRoute

This class asks for a start city and end city. It uses MapQuest to find a route (latitude/longitude on legs). It then uses Google Places to find places near the latitude/longitude of each leg of route.

java -cp '.:lib/*' org.placemap.tests.PlacesOnRoute

OR (FOR WINDOWS)

java -cp ".:lib\*" org.placemap.tests.PlacesOnRoute

############ UNIT TESTS ############

jUnit tests are not yet implemented.

############ LIB ############

contains the required libraries for json-lib.
